      <description>Lemons go well with chicken and here is a great slow cooker recipe which is easy to put together and then leave for your slow cooker to work its magic.
You can use 1 tbs of  bottled lemon juice in place of squeezing a lemon. Garlic is also a good paprika replacement. For variation you can [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ovalslowcookers.co.uk/best-slow-cooker-recipes/slow-cooker-lemon-chicken/"&gt;Slow Cooker Lemon Chicken&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.ovalslowcookers.co.uk"&gt;Oval Slow Cookers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



Other handy slow cooker posts:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.ovalslowcookers.co.uk/best-slow-cooker-recipes/slow-cooking-making-the-perfect-chicken-stock/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Slow Cooking: Making the Perfect Chicken Stock'&gt;Slow Cooking: Making the Perfect Chicken Stock&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/oval-slow-cookers/Oval_Slow_Cookers-Slow_Cooker_Lemon_Chicken.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Lemons" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/49503154413@N01/4278790223/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4071/4278790223_44f7576961_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Lemons" /></a>Lemons go well with chicken and here is a great slow cooker recipe which is easy to put together and then leave for your slow cooker to work its magic.</p>
<p>You can use 1 tbs of  bottled lemon juice in place of squeezing a lemon. Garlic is also a good paprika replacement. For variation you can also try this dish using Orange juice and a fresh orange, or even using limes.</p>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p>
<p>4 chicken breasts, boned and skinless<br /> 1 fresh lemon<br /> 1 tsp. pepper<br /> 1 tsp. paprika</p>
<p><strong>Instructions:</strong></p>
<p>Place the chicken breasts in the bottom of the slow cooker<br /> Slice the lemon in half and squeeze the juice from 1/2 over the chicken.<br /> Sprinkle the pepper and paprika over the chicken.<br /> Slice the remaining half of lemon into thin slices.<br /> Put the lemon slices on top of the chicken.<br /> Cover and slow cook on high 4 hours.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="geishaboy500" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/49503154413@N01/4278790223/" target="_blank">geishaboy500</a></small></p>
<p> </p>
