      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="crocked 11.13.09 [317]" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10343926@N02/4107943705/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2488/4107943705_bca4d5d877_m.jpg" border="0" alt="crocked 11.13.09 [317]" /></a>Buying a slow cooker doesn&#8217;t have to be hard. I&#8217;ve placed some of my hottest tips below to help you make the right decision.</p>
<p><strong>What Size Slow Cooker Do I Need?</strong></p>
<p>Slow cookers can be bought in various sizes, but usually fit into three groups.</p>
<p>Mini slow cookers are around 1.5 litres and are best for the single cook or a couple who want to use a slow cooker for a single meal.</p>
<p>Medium sized slow cookers can hold 3.5 litres but have a usual cooking capacity of about 2.5 litres. They&#8217;re great for slow cooking meals for 2-4 people.</p>
<p>Large slow cookers have a capacity of 6 litres which works out as about 4.5 litres in the pot. Ideal for large groups or for batch cooking, for example, bulk cooking stews and casseroles to divide and freeze.</p>
<p>The difference in size and actual cooking capacity happens because you need to have some spare space in a slow cooker in order for the food to cook properly.</p>
<p><strong>How Do I Clean My Slow Cooker?</strong></p>
<p>Slow cookers include inner ceramic pots which can be removed to allow you to serve your slow cooking straight from the slow cooker to the dinner table. This removable dish lets your guests or family sit and relax at the table as they serve their food straight onto the plate instead of you standing over the stove to dish up. Many inner pots are non-stick and most can be placed straight into a dishwasher making cleaning up at the end of your meal as easy as making it in the first place</p>
<p><strong>How Do I Work Out The Temperature I Need?</strong></p>
<p>Temperature settings vary amongst different types of slow cookers. Most have a range of temperature settings to meet the needs of various recipes. Some have just a couple of settings (low and high) and others include five settings that vary from high (two hours) to really slow cooking (ten hours or more). Some even have a warm setting in case your dish has finished cooking but the accompanying side dishes still need to be prepared or finish cooking. This setting is also very useful for those occasions when everyone isn’t ready to eat their meal just yet.</p>
<p> </p>
